headline.main: 1943 PLANE OUTPUT TO DWARF LAST YEAR'S; Curtiss-Wright Official Sees Attainment of 'Impossible'

lead_paragraph: Although the American aviation industry during the past year performed "miracles" in production, it is expanding its output in 1943 to what was once considered "impossible" proportions, according to G.W. Vaughan, president of Curtiss-Wright Corporation and head of the Aircraft War Production Council, East Coast, Inc.
abstract: '42-43 survey by G W Vaughn, Aircraft War Production Council, East Coast, head
